### Finding 4 ‚Äî No retry before FAIL

- `_execute_probe()` in `daily_probe.py` (lines 157-226) is a single
  `urllib.request.urlopen(...)` call inside one `try` block. No retry loop, no
  `failure_threshold`, no exponential backoff.
- `Probe` dataclass (line 94) has only `name`, `path`, `accepted_status_codes` ‚Äî
  no `failure_threshold` field.
- A `bearings-v1.service` restart overlapping the 09:15¬±5min window (per
  `bearings-v1-probe.timer:18 RandomizedDelaySec=5min`) produces an immediate
  `url_error reason='Connection refused'` and exit 1 ‚Üí FAIL log entry.
- Verdict: STILL_OPEN.

### Finding 5 ‚Äî No log retention policy

- `daily_probe.py` `_build_arg_parser()` (lines 313-346) declares only
  `--base-url`, `--log-dir`, `--timeout`, `-q/--quiet`. No `--max-age-days`,
  `--retention-days`, or any cleanup flag.
- `grep "max-age|max_age|logrotate|retention|cleanup"` against
  `scripts/daily_probe.py` ‚Üí no matches.
- `grep` against full `scripts/` dir surfaces only `cutover_smoke.py` tempdir
  cleanup (unrelated; that's `shutil.rmtree` for the cutover workdir).
- `bearings-v1-probe.service` has no `ExecStartPost` cleanup, no tmpfiles.d
  conf in `config/`, no logrotate snippet.
- `~/.local/share/bearings-v1/probes/YYYY-MM-DD.log` therefore accumulates
  indefinitely. Same hole exists for
  `~/.local/share/bearings-v1/diff-probes/YYYY-MM-DD.log`.
- Verdict: STILL_OPEN.

